Nigeria Plans to Boost Rice, Cocoa, Cotton Output, Vanguard Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-09-09T08:39:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/nigeria-plans-to-boost-rice-cocoa-cotton-output-vanguard-says.html
Nigeria plans to increase output of
rice, cassava, sorghum, cocoa and cotton over four years in a
410 billion-naira ($2.6 billion) investment plan aimed at
creating 3.5 million jobs,  Vanguard reported , citing Minister of
Agriculture Akinwunmi Adeshina.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 